The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Aug. 19: i-flex America Inc, the wholly-owned subsidiary of i-flex Solutions Ltd, has exercised the modified option agreement, gaining a minimum of 51 per cent ownership stake in the equity of Canada?s Castek. The company had bought the options in March 2005. 

 New Delhi, Aug. 19: The board of Kajaria Ceramics will meet on August 26 to consider stock split and raising capital from the overseas market. The company plans to split a share of Rs 10 to five stocks of Rs two each. It will also consider issuing GDR or FCCBs up to $3 crore for capital expenditure. 

 Mumbai, Aug. 19: Colgate-Palmolive (India) Ltd has set up a toothpaste manufacturing facility at Baddi in Himachal Pradesh at an investment of Rs 105 crore. The plant is spread over 36,000 sq meters and employs around 200 people.

 Calcutta, Aug. 19: Stone India Ltd will set up a greenfield manufacturing project at Baddi in Himachal Pradesh. To part finance the new project and foraying into new areas of business, the company had decided to raise Rs 14.55 crore through 15 lakh convertible warrants.

 Mumbai, Aug. 19: Amtek India Ltd will raise $75 million by issuing GDRs or FCCBs. The company has also declared a dividend of 20 per cent on the paid-up share capital.




